results.output_text: Speculative decoding is a technique used in large language models to accelerate text generation by predicting and precomputing multiple future tokens in parallel, then selectively accepting or rejecting them based on correctness. This reduces the computational burden of repeatedly recomputing the same steps, improving throughput without sacrificing accuracy.
